## What was built

**New modular architecture** — fully working, all imports/smoke-tests pass:

```
sim/flight_modes.py       FlightMode enum (STABILIZE=0 … RECOVERY=7)
sim/aircraft_dynamics.py  Re-exports AircraftPhysics from existing aircraft.py
sim/mission_manager.py    MissionManager — loads JSON, advances segments, exposes TargetInfo
sim/rewards.py            compute_reward() — dispatches to 8 per-mode reward functions
envs/fixed_wing_env.py    FixedWingEnv — 27-D obs, 4-D action, training + mission modes
render/pygame_renderer.py Renderer class — chase camera, 3D projection, aircraft model, HUD
missions/demo_mission.json Takeoff → waypoint × 2 → loiter → approach → landing
train.py                  Headless PPO (DummyVecEnv, no threading) → models/fixed_wing_multimode_ppo.zip
visualize.py              Pygame opens immediately, model inference only, keyboard 1-8/R/ESC
main.py                   python main.py train|visualize|demo
requirements.txt
```

**Run training:**
```
python main.py train --timesteps 300000
```

**Run visualization** (opens window immediately, falls back to random actions if no model):
```
python main.py visualize
```

**Keyboard in visualize:**  `1-8` force flight mode · `R` reset · `ESC` quit

The old `envs.py` / `aircraft.py` / original `main.py` are untouched — both systems coexist.
